<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="JAS" stage="Rev" version="B">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 04:07:21Z" when="2009-10-02 04:07:21Z" stage="Draft">drafted by Pdt. Max. Jacob; consultants C &amp; B Grimes; June &amp; Chuck exegetical pass December 2001, Darwin; TW3, Morris, Exeg. Summ. Trans Handbook; David's comm. on James (in TW3), UNS check; Kupang, Gereja Paulus, 31 Jan, 2002; Chuck, Max &amp; Mus; Consultant check with David Glasgow and Max, Mus, and Chuck at Gereja Silo, Kupang, 24-25 April 2002; Gk notes added by Chuck Sept 2005, checked Christ &amp; devil; further exegetical changes in Oct 2005 with Marge Crofts, Barbara &amp; Chuck marked with (***); read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 11:15:11Z" when="2014-02-24 11:15:11Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 24-25 April 2002 at Gereja Silo in Kupang; Consultant: David Glasgow, approved. Report: KM James consltnt check.doc.</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-22 02:26:57Z" when="2015-01-22 02:26:57Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read through for Kupang mini-Bible with Chuck, Lena, Rina, Oma at UBB. BackTrans also adjusted.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Yakobis</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Surat dari pamimpin gareja di pusat, nama<bt>Letter from the church leader at the centre, named</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Yakobis<bt>Yakobis</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pusat ; Yakobis, Kobis ; pamimpin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">pusat ; Yakobis, Kobis ; pamimpin = implies kapala ; pimpinan = implies one of several</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Salam<bt>Greetings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Salam dari beta, Yakobis. Beta ni, Tuhan Allah deng kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, pung orang suru-suru.<bt>Greetings from me, Yakobis. I am God and Boss Yesus Kristus' *servant (=person to be ordered around).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta tulis ini surat kasi bosong orang Yahudi yang su iko sang Tuhan Yesus, yang ada maranto pi mana-mana.<bt>I write this letter to you-pl Yahudi people who already follow/obey the Lord Yesus, who are working outside home country everywhere.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maranto"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">maranto</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doûlos: well-known slave dóodeka phylaîis: Jewish"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">doûlos: well-known slave dóodeka phylaîis: Jewish or symbolic or only Jewish Christians?<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>diasporâai: living in many communities away from their true home, like Hawaiians on the mainland. the true home might be Jerusalem, or heaven</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;kasi 12 suku-bangsa yang idop tasiar&gt;&gt;. Deng bagitu, Yakobis tulis dia pung surat kasi orang Yahudi dong yang su sarani. Ma dia pung nasiat di sini kaná deng samua orang Kristen.<bt>The Yunani language says “to 12 tribes who are living scattered”. In that way, Yakobis was writing his letter to the Yahudi people who are already baptised/christianised. But his advice here is effective for all Christians.</bt></note><note reference="1:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 13:55, Markus 6:3, Utusan dong pung Carita 15:13, Galatia 1:19</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo dapa susa, na, batahan deng parcaya sang Tuhan sa<bt>If/when (you) get difficulty, na, just persevere in believing / persevere and believe in God1</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Sodara dong! Beta mau kasi tau bagini: kalo bosong kaná susa macam-macam, na, jang pata samangat. Tarima sa deng hati sanáng, te nanti dia pung hasil bae.<bt>Siblings! I want to tell you this: if/when you-pl experience various sorts of difficulty, na, don't become discouraged/ lose hope/despair. Receive/accept it with a glad heart, cuz (elaboration) later there will be a good result.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="upa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">upa</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="charàn: like the beatitudes. but here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">charàn: like the beatitudes. but here it's long term joy, and in 9ff. poikílois: diverse situations<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>peripéseete: run into unpleasant testing situations without trying to peirasmoîs: opportunities for doing wrong, tests where you could foul up<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>hótan: this may go better at the beginning</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te kotong tau bilang, kalo bosong batahan dalam susa bagitu, deng su lolos dari coba'an, deng bosong masi parcaya tarús sang Tuhan, itu bekin bosong tamba tanáng kalo dapa coba'an laen.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-inc know that when you-pl persevere/endure in difficulty in that way, and have successfully.come.out.other.side of the test/trial/ordeal, and you-pl still continue to believe in God1, that will make you increase in calmness if/when you encounter other difficulties.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lolos = come out the other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">lolos = come out the other end ; cobaan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dokímion: in spite of testing situations"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">dokímion: in spite of testing situations in 2 tò: going through it all<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Bosong sonde usa bale balakang dari susa. Ma biar ko bosong bisa balajar tahan susa sampe bosong jadi langkáp. Deng bagitu, bosong jadi sampurna, deng sonde kurang satu apa ju.<bt>You-pl do not need to turn your back on difficulty. But allow yourselves to be able to learn to endure difficulty to the point that you are complete1/equipped. In that way, you-pl will be complete2/well-rounded, and not lacking anything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="flek ~ noda = spot, fleck"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">flek ~ noda = spot, fleck ; watak = character, nature (mesolectal)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="érgon téleion: do everything it should"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">érgon téleion: do everything it should dokímion: being tested in a lot of ways<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>téleioi: just like what you're aiming to be: same word as "all da way" holókleeroi: all the parts in working order: change order in pidgin<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>leipómenoi: same idea from the negative side: nothing essential missing</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo kotong minta satu hal dari Tuhan, jang minta deng hati bacabang<bt>If/when we-inc ask something from God1, don't ask with a branched liver (=doubting, double-minded)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Kalo ada dari bosong yang rasa diri sonde tau jalan kaluar dari susa, bosong bisa tanya sang Tuhan yang tau samua. Dia yang bisa kasi tunju jalan kaluar kasi sang bosong. Dia yang buka jalan deng hati sanáng, deng Dia sonde mara sang bosong kalo bosong minta sang Dia.<bt>If there is someone from among you-pl who feels himself not knowing the way out of difficulty, you-pl can ask God1 who knows everything. He is the one who can show the way out for you-pl. He is the one who gladly forges the path/opens the way, and He is not angry with you-pl if/when you ask Him. [EXEG: a number of commentators (see Ex. Summ for a start) have pointed out that this is not open-ended generic wisdom, but wisdom in how to handle the difficulties introduced in vs. 2-4.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati bacabang = hati mendua (BI),"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">hati bacabang = hati mendua (BI), hati muka-balakang (KM), doubt ; jalan pende ~ jalan potong = shortcut or escape</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tis hymôon: generic &quot;you&quot; for &quot;anybody&quot;:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">tis hymôon: generic "you" for "anybody": "one a" is mesolectal leípetai: same greek root as "missing" in 4<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>sophías: practical wisdom in life situations oneidízontos: scold, give grudgingly<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ma kalo minta sang Dia, jang minta deng hati bacabang. Bosong musti parcaya batúl bilang, Dia bisa kasi apa yang bosong minta. Te kalo orang yang minta deng hati bacabang, dia sama ke galombang yang angin fuu barmaen ko nae-turun sonde karuang.<bt>But if/when (you) ask Him, don't ask with a forked liver (=doubting, double-minded). You-pl must truly believe that He is able to give what you-pl are asking for. Cuz (elaboration) if/when a person asks with a forked liver, s/he is like waves which the wind blows around (=playing) so that it ascends-descends without order/pattern.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karuang = teratur, rapi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">karuang = teratur, rapi</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aiteítoo: admonition about asking diakrinómenos: vacillating"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">aiteítoo: admonition about asking diakrinómenos: vacillating about whether god will come across<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>klýdooni thalássees: open ocean, not surf anemizoménooi kaì rhipizoménooi: greek uses two near synonymous verbs: "drive with wind" and "fan out": conflate?<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>rhipizoménooi: variable wind, not steady</Message></Annotation><v n="7-8" />Orang yang gampang tagoyang bagitu, sonde stabil deng samua parkara. Jang harap ko dia dapa apa-apa dari Tuhan.<bt>People who are easily moved/shaken like that, are not stable in anything (=in every matter). Don't hope/expect him to get anything from God1.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="appositive construction OR COMBINE 7-8 so"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">appositive construction OR COMBINE 7-8 so the "not goin get anyting" part comes last as the punch line? ho ánthroopos ekeînos: (generic)<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>aneèr: who, if this part goes into 7 akatástatos: implies instability<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang kasian, deng orang kaya<bt>Poor/unfortunate/miserable people and rich people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Orang kasian yang su parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus, dong musti bekin dong pung hati babunga, tagal Tuhan Allah ada angka ame sang dong jadi Dia pung kelu.<bt>Poor/unfortunate/miserable people who already believe in the Lord Yesus, they must make their livers flowered (be happy/joyful), because God has elevated/adopted them to be His family/kin.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasang mata = watch over, perhatikan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">pasang mata = watch over, perhatikan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho adelphòs: generic, not anybody specific"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">ho adelphòs: generic, not anybody specific in mind. plural? tapeinòs: outward circumstances, bottom socioeconomic class<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>kauchásthoo: brag -- not same as 2, but close hýpsei: make him hold his head high because of what god does for him, now or hereafter. dignity<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10-11" />Deng orang kaya yang su parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus, dia ju musti bekin hati babunga, tagal Tuhan ajar dia ko jang sombong. Sakarang dia mangarti bilang, dia pung harta dong nanti ilang buang, sama ke bunga utan yang babunga bagus, ma sonde lama te matahari panggang sang dia ko dia layu buang. Bagitu ju deng orang kaya. Biar dong batasibu deng dong pung urusan, ma dong ju ilang buang.<bt>And rich/powerful person/people who already believe in the Lord Yesus, he must also make his liver flowered (be happy/joyful), because God1 has taught him to not be proud/arrogant. Now s/he must understand that his belongings/possessions will completely disappear/be lost, just like a wild flower which blossoms beautifully, but it's not long before the sun roasts it so it withers up/away. It's the same way also with rich people. Even though they're fussing about with all their business/affairs, nevertheless they will also disappear. [EXEG: NRSV, NLT, TH, Ex Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Following discussion in Trans. Handbook. randa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">Following discussion in Trans. Handbook. randa hati (one UNS says BI) ; panggang ; layu ; harta ; orang kaya ; urusan *** last sentence revised to include the rich, not just their affairs</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho dè ploúsios: also generic, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">ho dè ploúsios: also generic, and parallel to 9 tapeinoósei: parallel to 9, result of decisive action "take him down a peg"<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>anéteilen: timeless aorist en taîs poreíais autoû marantheésetai: the more he plugs away at his business, the more he shrivels up or fades away, probably referring to becoming poorer and poorer<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:10-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:6-7</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Samua yang bae datang dari Tuhan, ma hal jahat sonde datang dari Dia<bt>Everything that is good comes from God1, but evil things don't come from Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Tuhan kasi berkat sang orang yang tahan coba'an sampe lolos. Ais ju dia tarima dia pung upa idop yang Tuhan su janji kasi orang yang sayang sang Dia. Dia tarima dia pung upa sama ke orang yang juara tarima piala.<bt>God1 gives blessing to people who endure tests/ordeals to.point.that they come.successfully.through.other.side. So then s/he receives his life reward which God1 has promised to people who love Him. He receives his reward just like a champion person receives a champions.cup.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kandang singa = den of lions"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">kandang singa = den of lions (Idiom = terlepas dari cobaan, bahaya, marabahaya) BI = sarang penyamun; atlet = athlete</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aneèr: (generic) makários: this is the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">aneèr: (generic) makários: this is the Greek word used in the beatitudes: fortunate<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>leémpsetai tòn stéphanon: reward</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;dia tarima στέφανος (<span class="Italic">stefanos</span>) idop&gt;&gt;. <span class="Italic">Stefanos</span> tu, satu topi yang dong kasi sang atlet yang dapa juara satu.<bt>The Yunani language says “s/he receives a στέφανος (<span class="Italic">stefanos</span>) of life”. That <span class="Italic">stefanos</span>, is a kind of hat which they gave to an athlete who was the number one champion.</bt></note></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\BK00157C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Orang Yunani kasi topi juara sang orang yang manáng<bt>The Greeks gave a champion's hat to the person who won</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Inga bae-bae! Kalo ada dari bosong yang kaná coba'an deng kapingin mau bekin sala, jang tudu bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu, Tuhan yang coba sang beta!&gt;&gt; Te Tuhan Allah sonde parná ada kapingin bekin sala. Deng Dia sonde parná coba orang ko itu orang kapingin bekin sala.<bt>Remember well! If there is from among you-pl who experiences/encounters testing/ordeal and wants/desires to do wrong, don't be accusing saying, “It was God1 who tested/tempted me!” Cuz (elaboration) God has never had a desire to do wrong/sin. And He has never tested/tempted a person so that person wanted to do wrong.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peirazómenos: opportunity to do wrong, incentive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">peirazómenos: opportunity to do wrong, incentive to sin apeírastós estin kakoôn: untouched by the desire to to wrong, has nothing to do with<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Te sala kaluar dari orang pung hati sandiri. Partama, dia pung hati ada kapingin mau bekin jahat, ais dia mulai putar otak bekin rancana kotor.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) wrong/sin comes out from a person's own liver. At first, his liver desires to do wrong, and.so he begins to churn his brain (=scheme) to make evil2/dirty plans.</bt><v n="15" />Ais ju dia bekin, iko dia pung rancana kotor tu. Dia pung ujung, andia, Tuhan Allah kasi jato hukuman mati sang orang yang bekin jahat.<bt>And so he does it, according to his dirty plans. In the end/tip, God hands down the death penalty to people who do evil.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Sodara sayang dong! Jang kaná tipu so'al ini samua.<bt>Dear siblings! Don't be deceived about all these things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adelphoí mou agapeetoí: loved brothers and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">adelphoí mou agapeetoí: loved brothers and sisters, fellow Christians -- good [Christian] friends planaâsthe fool yourselves (reflexive), let anyone fool you (middle), get tricked (passive)<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Hal jahat dong sonde kaluar dari Tuhan. Ma Dia kasi datang samua berkat yang bae deng samua hal yang barisi. Dia yang bekin matahari, bulan, deng bintang dong. Dong samua bapinda-pinda di langit, deng itu bekin dong pung bayang-bayang ba'oba tarús. Cuma Tuhan Allah sa yang sonde tau ba'oba.<bt>Evil things don't come.out from God1. But He gives (toward us) all blessings which are good and all things that are clean/pure. He is the one who has made the sun and moon and stars. They all move continually in the sky, and that makes their shadows change continually. Only God alone is what does not change (at all).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lempar tulang sambunyi tangan = melakukan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">lempar tulang sambunyi tangan = melakukan sst tapi tidak mau bertanggungjawab</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apò toû patròs phoótoon: sun, moon,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">apò toû patròs phoótoon: sun, moon, stars parallageè variation: stays the same<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>tropeês turning, motion, change aposkíasma shadow that is cast<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Tuhan pung rancana kasi kotong bagini: Dia kasi Dia pung Kata-kata yang batúl sang kotong. Deng Dia pake Dia pung Kata-kata tu, ko kasi idop sang kotong. Dari samua yang Dia bekin di ini dunya, Dia su pili ame kotong jadi Dia pung ulu hasil.<bt>God1's plan for us-inc is like this: He gives His true Words to us-inc. And He uses those Words of His, to make us live/to give life to us-inc. From among everything which He has made in this world, He has chosen us-inc to be his first.fruits (first, choice, set aside from the rest).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rancana ; ulu hasil = first"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">rancana ; ulu hasil = first fruits (first, choice, set aside from the rest)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apekýeesen: give us spiritual life If"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">apekýeesen: give us spiritual life If apekyeesen is taken as "make us his kids", that is not necessarily a hanai (adoptive) relationship, so we would need to review all the adoption passages (hyiothesia and others).<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>tina: James feels the metaphor is not very accurate</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dengar, deng bekin iko Tuhan pung Kata-kata<bt>Hear/listen, and do according to God1's Words</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Sodara sayang dong! Inga, é! Parinsip yang bae, bagini: orang jang omong asal babunyi sa. Ada lebe bae, kalo orang laen omong yang bae, dia pasang talinga ko dengar bae-bae dolo! Deng orang jang gampang nae dara.<bt>Dear siblings! Remember this! A really good principle is this: people/a person shouldn't speak just to make noise (=without thinking). It is best, if/when another person is saying something good, s/he fastens his ears to listen carefully first! And people should not be quick-tempered.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="omong asal babunyi = omong sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">omong asal babunyi = omong sonde pake pikir, omong tanpa pikir, sonde kana sasaran (asbun = BI asal bunyi) ; gampang nae dara = quick-tempered ; nae daon = his position has gotten to his head ; mati badiri = ?? ; prinsip</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adelphoí mou agapeetoí: loved brothers and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">adelphoí mou agapeetoí: loved brothers and sisters as in 16 íste: what he just said? general knowledge? statement? command?<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>tachùs eis tò akoûsai: willing to learn</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Te kalo mara, orang sonde bisa bekin hal bae, iko Tuhan Allah pung mau.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if people get mad, they cannot do good things, according to God's will.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Jadi bosong musti bakar buang bosong pung sala-sala dong samua. Sama ke orang tofa kasi barisi dia pung kabón, ais bakar buang dia pung kotoran. Deng bosong ju musti tarima deng randá hati Tuhan pung Kata-kata. Itu Kata-kata dong sama ke bibit yang ada tatanam di bosong pung dalam hati. Kalo bosong bekin bagitu, nanti Tuhan kasi lapás sang bosong dari bosong pung sala-sala dong, deng Dia tarima bosong ko bosong idop tarús deng Dia.<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must (make the effort) to burn off all of your wrongs. Just like a person weeds his garden/field to make it clean, and then burns off the filth/rubbish. And you-pl must also receive humbly (&lt;low liver) God's Words. Those Words are like seeds which are planted [+agentless construction] in your-pl livers. If/when you-pl do that, then God1 will free you from your wrongs, and He will receive/accept you so you can/will live continually with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bakar buang = implies effort ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">bakar buang = implies effort ; randa hati = humble, rendah hati ; tatanam ; ilang buang = s.t. get lost unintentionally ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="émphyton: like planting a plant in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">émphyton: like planting a plant in the ground</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi kasi ilang samua yang sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">Jadi kasi ilang samua yang sonde batúl dari bosong pung idop, bae lahir, bae batin. Deng hati yang renda bosong musti tarima deng sanang kabar bésar yang kotong su tarima ame, yang bagitu tia idop dalam kotong pung hati ju dia kasi salamat kotong samua pung jiwa dong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Deng kalo bosong su tau Tuhan pung Kata-kata, na, bosong musti bekin iko. Jang cuma dengar sa! Kalo bosong cuma dengar sa, ma sonde bekin iko, bosong putar-balek deng bosong pung diri sandiri.<bt>And if you-pl already know God1's Words, na, you-pl must do according to them. Don't just listen only! If you just listen only, but don't do according (to them), you are deceiving your very own selves.</bt><v n="23-24" />Kalo orang su dengar ame itu Kata-kata, ma sonde bekin iko, itu tingka ke orang yang loti dia pung muka di carmín. Bagitu dia bale balakang kasi tenga itu carmín, ju dia lupa buang memang dia pung pasmén.<bt>If a person has heard/listened to those Words, but doesn't do according to them, that is like a person who inspects/glances at his face in a mirror, and immediately forgets his style/image/appearance. [EXEG: Because vs. 24 explicitly addresses "forgetting", I (CEG) have chosen not to follow NLT's "addition" of "but doing nothing to improve your appearance". While it is a very attractive application from the context, it seems to have no justification from the text itself. So it is hard to find a translation principle that warrants it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="carmín = ; pasmén = bastel,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">carmín = ; pasmén = bastel, gaya ; @@ rethink: dengar ame &gt; dengar ;</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Ma bosong jang barenti pareksa bae-bae Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata yang langkáp, yang bisa kasi lapás sang orang dari dia pung sala-sala dong. Tuhan nanti kasi berkat dalam samua hal yang bosong ada bekin, asal bosong dengar deng bekin iko itu Kata-kata. Jang cuma maso talinga kiri, ais kaluar talinga kanan!<bt>But you-pl should not stop examining/inspecting/investigating well/thoroughly God's Words that are complete, which can free people from their wrongs. God1 will give blessing in everything which you-pl are doing, as long as you listen to and do according to those Words. Don't just (let it) go in the left ear, and then exit the right ear! [DISCOURSE: Popular local saying, reinforcing the point.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Check out all James's &quot;law&quot; passages,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">Check out all James's "law" passages, because rather than contrasting law and gospel, he lumps them together into God's total package. It's almost as if he were treating "trust Christ" as the 11th Commandment. 1:25, 2:8-12, 4:11-12. But it isn't quite the regular technical term for "Gospel" either. "Everyting God tell his peopo dey gotta do" seems to cover both sides. eleutherías: in pidgin, used heavily for "no charge", but rarely for "out of custody". Here it's very close to "salvation", freedom from sin<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>nómos "God's Rules" is a tongue-twister for F Chun because of the 's. "Rules from God" is more pronounceable</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Kalo orang anggap diri orang alim, ma sonde tau jaga dia pung mulu, itu orang tipu dia pung diri sandiri! Dia pung agama parcuma sa.<bt>If a person considers himself religious/pious, but doesn't know how to guard/be careful with his mouth, that person deceives2 his own self! His religion is ineffectual/in vain.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="alim = religious, pious, (but check"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">alim = religious, pious, (but check if considered KM or BI) ; ~ rajin agama</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apatoon kardian autou: deceiving his own"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">apatoon kardian autou: deceiving his own heart</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Te agama yang barisi tu, sonde ada pung kamomos apa-apa. Itu yang bekin sanáng Tuhan Allah Bapa pung hati. Agama yang batúl bagitu, bekin orang suka bantu mama-mama janda deng ana yatim-piatu dong. Orang yang pung agama macam bagitu, sonde kasi biar orang dalam ini dunya pangaru sang dong deng parkara jahat.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) religion that is clean/pure, has no filth/defilement at all. It is that which pleases God the Father's liver. True religion of that sort, makes people like to help mama widows and orphan children. People who have that sort of religion don't allow people in this world to influence them with evil matters. [NOTE to daughter translations: If need fewer abstract nouns, or personification a problem consider: “people who stick to true religion of that sort help... and don't...]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agama ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">agama ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katharà PURE, NOTHING GETS IN THE"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">katharà PURE, NOTHING GETS IN THE WAY OF ASSOCIATING WITH GOD, OPPOSITE OF pilau amíantos UNSTAINED, NOTHING BAD<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>katharà kai amíantos ALREADY COVERED, OR DOES IT NEED A WRAPUP?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang bapili-pili bilang, orang bésar ko orang kici<bt>Don't go being selective/prejudiced/biased about whether a person is big/important/influential or small/unimportant/uninfluential</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara dong! Karmana ko bosong bisa bilang bosong parcaya sang Yesus Kristus, kotong pung Bos yang hebat, kalo bosong maen bapili muka? Jang bagitu!<bt>Siblings! How can you-pl say that you believe in Yesus Kristus, our-inc impressive/amazing Boss, if you are always/often showing bias/discrimination? Don't do that!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***reduce response to rhetorical question to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">***reduce response to rhetorical question to make speaker attitude (scolding) clear</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prosoopoleempsíais: discrimination based on appearance of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">prosoopoleempsíais: discrimination based on appearance of social position or wealth NRSV: My brothers and sisters, do you with your acts of favoritism really believe in our glorious Lord Jesus Christ?<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jang bekin rusak bosong pung parcaya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">Jang bekin rusak bosong pung parcaya deng cara bagitu!</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Andekata ada dua orang maso pi dalam bosong pung ruma sambayang. Satu pake pakean mangkilat, deng cincin mas ponu di tangan. Yang laen pake baju dadolek.<bt>If, for example, there were two people entering into your-pl house of worship. One wears bright/shining clothes, with gold rings full on his hands. The other wears a filthy/worn shirt/clothes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eiséltheei ... hymoôn: visitors, not regulars"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">eiséltheei ... hymoôn: visitors, not regulars ryparaâi: in bad shape, ragged shabby (of clothes), also used in a moral sense in 1:21<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ais bosong batasibu sambut sang itu orang yang pake pakean mangkilat, ko kasi dia tampa paling bae di muka. Ma yang pake baju dadolek tu, na, bosong suru bilang, &lt;&lt;Badiri di balakang sana! Kalo sonde, na, dudu di lante!&gt;&gt;<bt>So.then you-pl make yourselves busy greeting that person with the bright/shining clothes, to give him the best place in front. But the one who wears the filthy clothes, na, you-pl order him, saying “Stand in the back there! If not, na, sit on the floor!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaloôs: buttering him up or sucking"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">kaloôs: buttering him up or sucking up to him</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Deng bosong pung cara bapili muka bagitu, bosong sama ke tukang putus parkara yang sonde adil. Ada maksud jahat yang satír sang bosong bagitu.<bt>With the way that you are showing bias/prejudice like that, you-pl are just like a judge (&lt;person characterised by deciding court cases) who is not just/fair. There is an evil purpose which is steering/driving you like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="satír = drive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">satír = drive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diekrítheete: you have introduced divisions in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">diekrítheete: you have introduced divisions in your group dialogismoôn poneeroôn: use wrong standards in judging people, or rationalize your judgments based on bad ideas -- not "dirty-minded judges", but their thought processes are screwed up, or bad<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Sodara sayang dong! Tuhan Allah su pili ame orang kasian di ini dunya ko dong parcaya kuat sang Dia, sama ke dong pung dalam hati ada kaya. Deng Dia ju pili sang dong ko dong ju ada bagian di Tuhan Allah pung parenta, yang Dia su janji ko kasi pi orang yang sayang sang Dia.<bt>Dear siblings! God has chosen the poor/unfortunate/ miserable people in this world for them to believe strongly in Him, as if their inner spirit/core being (&lt;inner liver) is rich. And He has also chosen them so they have a role/part in God's Government/Rule, which He has promised to give to people who love Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bagean ~ bagian = bahagian, role,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">bagean ~ bagian = bahagian, role, portion, position, hak, rights, ; dalam hati = hati nurani, inner spirit, core being</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kleeronómous: shouldn't imply that God has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">kleeronómous: shouldn't imply that God has to die before they can get at their inheritance</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ma deng bosong bapili muka bagitu, bosong su bekin hina sang orang kasian dong. Padahal dong sonde bekin jahat apa-apa sang bosong. Lupa, ko? Itu orang kaya dong yang bola-bola sang bosong. Deng dong tu yang tukang cari gara-gara, yang maen raroso bawa bosong pi pangadilan. Dong dapa dia pung manis, ais bosong dapa dia pung ampas.<bt>But with you-pl discriminating in that way, you are insulting/humiliating/degrading the poor/unfortunate/ miserable people. When in fact, they haven't done anything evil to you. You must have forgotten, right? It is the rich people who have (Idiom) been knocking you around like a (soccer) ball. And they are the ones who are always looking for something to make trouble about, who drag you (along the ground) to the law.courts. They get what is sweet, and you get the dregs/waste/pulp [DISCOURSE: modelling on proverb built on metaphor of sugarcane--expansion of verse explicating higher-level theme].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Last sentence implied by higher level"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">Last sentence implied by higher level context. taro muka = perhatikan ; bale muka = sonde toe ; bekin hina = insult, humiliate, degrade, merendahkan ; bola-bola sang bosong = kick you around like a (soccer) ball ; pangadilan ; maen roroso = drag you (implies you are powerless) ; but not for beta pung baju maen roroso tarus. Proverb: Dong dapa dia pung manis, ais bosong dapa dia pung ampas. (picture from sugarcane) = BI Habis manis, sepah dibuang. (context of husband and wife)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katadynasteúousin: oppress, exploit, grind down hélkousin:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">katadynasteúousin: oppress, exploit, grind down hélkousin: force you to appear in court, where they know they can get the judges to rule against you -- literally, drag you into court sessions<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Bosong tu, Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong. Ma orang kaya dong yang maen omong bekin rusak Tuhan Yesus pung nama bae! Akurang ko bosong maen cari muka deng dong?<bt>You-pl are the Lord Yesus' people (=possessed, identified with, inherently associated.with). But it is the rich people who keep slandering (&lt;speaking to damage) the Lord Yesus' good name/reputation! So why do you keep currying favour (&lt;seeking face) with them?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ónoma tò epikleethèn eph' hymaâs: name"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">ónoma tò epikleethèn eph' hymaâs: name which was invoked over you = you were baptized in the name of Jesus Christ (Acts 2:38), and now everybody knows you are his</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Itu pantas kalo bosong bekin iko Tuhan pung atoran satu yang paling pantíng, yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu musti sayang orang laen dong, sama ke lu sayang lu pung diri sandiri.&gt;&gt; Itu atoran ada tatulis dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi.<bt>It is appropriate that you-pl do according to God1's regulation which is extremely/most important saying, “You-sg must love other people/outsiders, just like you love your own self.” That regulation is written in the Scriptures.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mentoi: The sentence break gives a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">mentoi: The sentence break gives a similar force nomos: as in 1:25, for James this is the Gospel and it includes the Mosaic law but goes beyond it. It is not presented as Law vs. Gospel the same way Paul presents it, but as the Law side of the Gospel. Try dropping "God's Rules" as a technical term in James, because of his different slant on it -- except at the punch line of the next few verses, where he does go into judicial ideas like "lawbreaker" and "guilty" and leaves off talking about the salvation that comes from taking God's whole message to heart, until verse 12, where he gets back to the big picture.<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>katà teèn grapheén: as the Scripture says (Leviticus 19:18, also quoted in Mark 12:31, Matthew 19:19 and 22:39, Luke 10:27, Galatians 5:14, Romans 13:9)</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 19:18</note><v n="9" />Ma kalo bosong bapili muka deng cuma ame hati sang orang kaya sa, bosong su langgar itu atoran dari Tuhan. Bosong su sala, iko Tuhan pung Atoran.<bt>But if you-pl are discriminating and only wanting to please the rich people, you-pl have already broken/violated that regulation from God1. You-pl are wrong/have sinned, according to God1's Law.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ame hati = perhatikan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">ame hati = perhatikan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hamartían ergázesthe: you commit sin, are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">hamartían ergázesthe: you commit sin, are guilty of sin elengchómenoi: convict, prove you wrong<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Orang yang bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran anteru, ma kalo dia langgar satu atoran sa, itu sama sa deng dia su langgar samua Atoran.<bt>People who do according to/obey God1's entire Law, but if s/he violates just one regulation, that is the same as s/he has violated the whole Law.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anteru ; atoran ; hukum"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">anteru ; atoran ; hukum</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Tuhan su kasi atoran bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang maen serong.&gt;&gt; Dia ju yang kasi atoran laen bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang bunu bekin mati orang.&gt;&gt; Jadi kalo bosong sonde maen serong, ma ada bunu bekin mati orang, itu sama sa deng bosong su langgar Tuhan pung Atoran.<bt>God1 has given a regulation saying, “Don't commit adultery” (&lt;conventionalised from ‘deviate from straight road’). He is also the one who gave another regulation saying, “Don't commit murder.” So (consequently), if you don't commit adultery, but you do murder someone, that is just the same you-pl have violated God1's Law.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="itu sama sa deng = that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">itu sama sa deng = that means, artinya</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:13, 14, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:17, 18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Jadi kalo bosong mau omong, ko, mau bekin satu hal, bosong musti inga bagini: Tuhan Allah yang nanti putus kalo kotong ada bekin iko Dia pung atoran ko sayang sang orang dong, ko sonde. Te itu atoran yang bisa kasi lapás sang kotong dari Tuhan pung hukuman.<bt>So (consequently), if/when you-pl want to speak, or, want to do something, you-pl must remember this: God is the one who will decide if we-inc are doing according to His regulation to love other people, or not. Cuz (elaboration) that regulation is what can free/spare us-inc from God1's punishment. [EXEG: from Ex. Summ. "law of freedom" = 1) law of love, (from vs. 8) [NLT] 2) gospel, 3) Mosaic law (from vs. 10-11 above); also in Jas 1:25 (where most say it means "gospel"); each one runs into trouble in trying to make it fit the larger context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed exegesis, follow NLT, reduced internal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">***changed exegesis, follow NLT, reduced internal clash</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nomos eleutherias: law of freedom ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">nomos eleutherias: law of freedom = Gospel, which for James is not in opposition to Law but takes Law to greater heights.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, kalo bosong mau omong, ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">Jadi, kalo bosong mau omong, ko mau bekin satu hal, bosong musti inga bagini: Tuhan Allah yang nanti putus kalo kotong ada bekin iko Dia pung Hukum ko sonde. Tagal Dia pung atoran dong bisa kasi lapás sang kotong dari Tuhan pung hukuman, asal kotong bekin iko itu Hukum samua.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Te Tuhan sonde kasi hati sang orang yang sonde ada pung rasa kasian sang orang laen dong. Ma kalo bosong ada pung rasa kasian sang orang laen, tantu Tuhan ju ada pung rasa kasian sang bosong. Bosong sonde usa taku tarima Tuhan pung hukuman, tagal Dia su itong memang itu samua.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God1 does not have mercy/pity (&lt;give liver) to people who have no compassion/sense of mercy on other people. But if you-pl have compassion/sense of mercy toward other people, certainly God1 will also have compassion for you-pl. You don't need to be afraid of receiving God1's punishment, because He has already counted/made note of all that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi hati = pity, mercy, ampong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">kasi hati = pity, mercy, ampong</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo kotong parcaya batúl-batúl sang Tuhan, kotong musti bekin iko Dia pung Kata-kata<bt>If we-inc truly believe in God1, we-inc must do/behave following/obeying His Words</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Sodara dong! Kalo orang bilang dia ada parcaya sang Tuhan, ma sonde bekin apa-apa ko kasi tunju dia pung parcaya, itu sonde ada dia pung guna apa-apa. Parcaya macam bagitu sonde bisa kasi salamat sang dia.<bt>Siblings! If a person says s/he believes/trusts in God1, but doesn't do anything to show/demonstrate that faith/belief of his/hers, it has no use at all (=it is pointless). Faith of that sort cannot save him.</bt><v n="15" />Andekata ada bu ko usi yang ada pung parlú batúl-batúl, tingka ke sonde ada pung pakean, ko, sonde ada pung makan hari-hari.<bt>Let's say, for example, there were an older brother or older sister who has a real need, such as thay had no clothes, or, they didn't have food for their daily needs.</bt><v n="16" />Kalo bosong cuma bilang, &lt;&lt;Jalan bae-bae, ó! Biar ko Tuhan kasi berkat sang lu! Jang maso angin, é! Jang mati lapar, é!&gt;&gt; Guna apa deng omong bagitu, kalo bosong sonde bekin apa-apa yang praktis ko bantu sang dong?<bt>If you-pl only say, “Go well, ó! May God1 bless you! Don't catch cold, é [NOTE: response to lack of clothes]! Don't die of hunger, é!” What use is it to talk that way, if you-pl don't do anything practical to help them?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="praktis (ada UNS yg bilang bukan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">praktis (ada UNS yg bilang bukan bhs Kupang); mulu besar sa</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tis ... ex hymoôn: one person"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">tis ... ex hymoôn: one person speaking for the whole Christian group hypágete en eireénee: normal Jewish "Good-bye" form, "May everything go well for you". PTDM Laydahs, leddahs; others laters, latas, FC latahs<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>óphelos: what good does it do? how does it help? doote: SK read this with "go give um", indicating it is an act of the will, not just something that happens.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Jadi sonde cukup deng bilang lu parcaya to'! Deng parcaya sa, ma sonde bekin iko itu parcaya, dia pung nama su bukan &lt;parcaya&gt; lai. Te bagitu sama ke parcaya yang su mati, yang sonde ada pung guna apa-apa.<bt>So (consequently), it's not enough to just say you believe [+particle 'only, exclusively, unique']! By just believing, but not doing/behaving according to that belief, its name isn't really ‘faith’ any more. Cuz (elaboration) that is like faith that has died, which has no use whatsoever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="to' = saja, hanya, unique, satu-satunya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">to' = saja, hanya, unique, satu-satunya ; Be cuma minum to', sonde makan ; Lu makan/tidor to' = You do nothing except eat/sleep</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ada orang bisa angka parkara bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang bisa sa parcaya sang Tuhan, deng sonde ada pung bekin hal bae. Orang laen dong bisa bekin hal bae sa, deng sonde bawa-bawa Tuhan.&gt;&gt; Ma dia pung masala bagini: bukti dari lu pung parcaya tu, andia lu pung bekin hal bae dong. Ma kalo lu sonde bekin hal bae, beta sonde bisa lia bukti dari lu pung parcaya. Beta bisa kasi tunju beta pung parcaya deng cara beta bekin hal bae dong.<bt>Someone could argue saying, “People can just believe in God1, and not do anything good. (Whereas) another person could just do good things, and not involve God1.” But the problem is like this: the proof/evidence of your faith is precisely found in doing good things. But if you-sg don't do good things, I can't see any evidence/proof of your faith. I can show/demonstrate my faith, by means of my doing good things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="masala = ; angka parkara ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">masala = ; angka parkara ; bawa-bawa = involving</Message></Annotation><v n="19-20" />Lu iko ajaran yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah tu, cuma Dia sandiri sa. Sonde ada yang laen lai.&gt;&gt; Bae ju! Ma setan dong lebe bae dari lu, tagal dong ju parcaya bagitu, sampe-sampe dong taku deng gamatar. Jadi jang pikir kata, &lt;&lt;Deng mangarti pake otak sa su cukup.&gt;&gt; Sonde!<bt>You follow the teaching which says, “God, is just He alone. There is no other.” That's good! But the demons are better than you, because they also believe like that, to.point.that they tremble with fear. So (consequently), don't think saying, &lt;&lt;Just understanding with the brain alone is enough.&gt;&gt; No!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***vs 19-20 numbers combined; no other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">***vs 19-20 numbers combined; no other changes; KM sets off vocative as new paragraph mangarti pake panta sa<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Bodo, é! Su jalás kata, parcaya yang sonde ada pung hasil apa-apa, sonde ada pung guna apa-apa ju.<bt>That's stupid, é! It's clear that faith which yields no results whatsoever, also has no use whatsoever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hasil ; guna"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">hasil ; guna</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kené: shallow, inconsequential person"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">kené: shallow, inconsequential person</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ame conto dari kotong pung ba'i Abraham. Tempo hari, dia bekin iko apa yang Tuhan parenta sang dia, deng bawa dia pung ana Isak ko taro di atas meja korban. Tagal itu, Tuhan Allah bilang, &lt;&lt;Abraham su bekin yang batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Take the example of Grandpa/Forefather Abraham. In those days he did following/obeying what God1 commanded him, and brought his child Isak to put on the sacrifice table (*altar). Because of that, God said, “Abraham has done what is right/correct/true.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="edikaioóthee: considered him a righteous person."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">edikaioóthee: considered him a righteous person. Romans 1:17 has: Gotta trus God. Den you can get um right wit him. Romans 5 has: cuz we wen trus God, az why we wen get um right wit him.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 22:1-14</note><v n="22" />Abraham parcaya sang Tuhan sampe dia tarima ko bekin iko Tuhan pung parenta tu. Jadi kotong dapa tau bilang, dia parcaya anteru-anteru sang Tuhan, tagal dia bekin iko itu parenta.<bt>Abraham believed in God1 to.point.that he accepted to do according to that command of God1's. So (consequently), we-inc can know that he believe whole-heartedly/completely in the Lord1, because he obeyed/followed that command.</bt><v n="23" />Jadi ini samua jadi sama ke yang ada tatulis dalam Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Abraham parcaya sang Tuhan, ais Tuhan cap sang dia, orang hati lurus.&gt;&gt; Deng ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Abraham tu, Tuhan pung tamán.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), all this happened just as was written in the *Scriptures, which says, “Abraham believed God1, and.so God1 received/accepted him as a person whose liver was straight/righteous/just.” And it is written saying, “That Abraham was God1's friend.”</bt><note reference="2:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 15:6, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 20:7, Yesaya 41:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Su jalás, aa? Kotong tau bilang, Tuhan tarima orang kalo dia pung parcaya sang Tuhan yang bekin dia suka bekin hal bae dong ju. Parcaya to' sonde cukup.<bt>It's all clear, right? We-inc know that God1 accepts/receives a person if his/her faith in God is what makes him like to do good things. Just believing alone is not enough.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Parcaya yang ada dia pung hasil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">Parcaya yang ada dia pung hasil di orang pung idop, itu baru parcaya yang batúl! Deng parcaya macam ke itu, baru Tuhan mau bilang kotong bekin yang batúl.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Conto laen lai dari mama Rahab, itu parampuan nakal dari jaman dolu. Waktu orang kota Yeriko dong cari ko mau bunu bekin mati orang Isra'el pung mata-mata, Rahab pi sambunyi ame sang dong. Deng dia suru sang dong ko lari kaluar iko jalan laen, ko orang jang dapa tangkap sang dong. Ais Tuhan cap sang dia, parampuan hati lurus, tagal dia pung bekin bae tu.<bt>Take another example from Mama Rahab, that whore/prostitute from an earlier era. When the people of the city of Yeriko were searching wanting to kill the spies of the Israel people, Rahab hid them. And she ordered/told them to flee along a different road/path, so people wouldn't be able to catch them. So God1 received/accepted her as a woman whose liver was straight/righteous/just, because she did that good thing.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mata-mata = spy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">mata-mata = spy</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yosua 2:1-21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Parcaya yang sonde ada pung hasil, sama ke badan yang sonde ada pung napas, andia, mati. Bagitu ju, kalo orang bilang dia parcaya sang Tuhan, ma sonde ada bekin hal yang bae ju, itu omong kosong sa! Itu bukan parcaya yang idop.<bt>Faith which doesn't yield/produce a result, is like a body which has no breath, that is, it is dead. It is the same if a person says s/he believes in God1, but does not do anything good as well, that's just nonsense/b.s.! That is not a faith which is alive.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pneúmatos: not a ghost, not a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">pneúmatos: not a ghost, not a disembodied evil spirit. heart? life? what's the difference between a living person and a corpse?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jaga mulu bae-bae<bt>Guard/watch your mouth well/carefully</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** title shortened for broader application"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">*** title shortened for broader application</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jaga mulu bae-bae ko jang badodol"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">Jaga mulu bae-bae ko jang badodol</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara dong! Ada banya orang mau mangajar orang parcaya dong. Itu bae sa! Ma inga te Tuhan Allah nanti pareksa lebe alus orang yang mangajar sang orang parcaya dong. Jadi sonde bole sambarang orang mangajar.<bt>Siblings! Many people want to teach believers. That's good! But remember/be warned, cuz (elaboration) God will examine/check/investigate in more detail people who teach believers. So (consequently), it shouldn't be that just anyone teaches/(you) shouldn't let just anyone teach.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sambarang ; badodol = cerewet, gosip"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">sambarang ; badodol = cerewet, gosip negatif,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meîzon kríma leempsómetha: we will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">meîzon kríma leempsómetha: we will be judged with greater strictness (by God) -- tighter standards</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00029c.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;horizontalPosition:right">Tali kekáng di kuda pung mulu<bt>Bit and bridle in a horse's mouth</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Kotong samua omong sala macam-macam. Ma orang yang bisa tahan dia pung mulu ko jang badodol, ju bisa ator dia pung idop anteru.<bt>All of us-inc say various things that are wrong. But a person who is able to restrain his mouth so she doesn't just speak thoughtlessly/out of control, can also manage/regulate/control his entire life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mulu badodol = omong macam-macam ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">mulu badodol = omong macam-macam ; mulu bagatal = gosip ; rem &gt; tahan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pollà: in many ways téleios aneèr:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">pollà: in many ways téleios aneèr: a perfect person, perfect Christian; mature, complete, flawless, all the parts in working order<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ame conto dari kuda. Kotong bisa ator kuda bésar ko iko kotong pung mau, deng cuma hela dia pung tali kekáng sa.<bt>Take the example from a horse. We-inc can manage/control a large horse to follow/obey our desires, by merely pulling its bit rope.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="chalinoùs: tried to reproduce word play"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">chalinoùs: tried to reproduce word play with chalinagoogeesai by "handle ... handle", but it didn't work. peíthesthai: persuade, bring him to our way of thinking. Is "handle" more psychological, = "cope"?<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Conto laen lai dari kapal. Angin karás fuu barmaen kapal bésar iko dia pung suka. Ma papan kamudi kici sa bisa ator itu kapal pung jalan, iko nakoda pung mau.<bt>Take another example from a ship. A strong wind blows a big ship around (all over the place) as it wishes. But just a tiny steering board (=rudder) can control that ship's direction/journey, obeying the ship.captain's desires.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nakoda / kapten / juragan ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">nakoda / kapten / juragan = team and UNS dividied as to which is Kupang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anémoon skleeroôn: harsh winds beating on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">anémoon skleeroôn: harsh winds beating on sturdy sailing ships -- gale force, giving the crew trouble. Can "handle" be used for what a boat can do? check with sailing canoe people [OK]. "hard wind" implies "no can handle"; "bite hard" implies "almos no can" euthýnontos: pilot, steersman (the person at the rudder, not the captain). "boat driva" would be the captain; the "steersman" or "ho'ala guy" actually moves the steering oar (ho'ala), according to a Pidgin-speaking member of the crew of the Hokule'a sailing canoe. "Guy in charge a da steering"?<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Bagitu ju deng kotong pung mulu. Mulu tu, kici. Ma dia pung pakariang bésar mati pung!<bt>It is the same way with our-inc mouth. The mouth is small. But it's work/deeds/effects/impact are huge! [NOTE to daughter translations: Adapt ftn examples to local language. Don't translate!]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** ftn added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">*** ftn added</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:5" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani ada tulis bilang, &lt;lida&gt;. Ma di Yakobis 3:5-10, Yakobis ada tulis so'al orang pung omong. Kalo bahasa Kupang omong so'al orang pung omong, na, kotong sonde bilang &lt;lida&gt;, ma kotong biasa bilang &lt;mulu&gt;. Conto ke: basambung mulu, mulu badodol, mulu bagatal, mulu baminya, mulu banya, mulu bésar, mulu kotor, mulu manis, mulu panas, mulu panjang, mulu panta ayam, tukang bawa mulu, dll.<bt>The Yunani language writes ‘tongue’. But in verses 3:5-10 Yakobis is writing about people speaking/about what people say. When the Kupang language talks about people speaking/about what people say, na, we-inc don't say ‘tongue’, but we say ‘mouth’. For example: (all idioms using ‘mouth’) discuss/debate, say whatever comes to mind, gossip1, smooth talker, talkative1, boast, foul mouthed, sweet talker, rude, gossip2, and talkative2/fussy/fault-finding, tattle-tale, etc.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu sama ke bunga api kici yang bisa bakar abis utan anteru.<bt>It is like a small spark which can burn up an entire forest/bushland.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bunga api = spark ; lida"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">bunga api = spark ; lida api = flame ; arang manyala ; manyala ; kayu bakar ; fuu api ; kipas api ; bekin api = menyalakan api ; bakar tungku = make fire in the hearth</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hee gloosa: generic &quot;yoa mout&quot; rather"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">hee gloosa: generic "yoa mout" rather than "da mout", which in the context of ships could be a river mouth: FC</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Mulu tu, sama ke lida api. Kotong bisa pake kotong pung mulu ko bekin rusak banya hal. Kotong pung mulu bisa bekin ancor kotong pung idop anteru. Banya parkara jahat di ini dunya kaluar dari orang pung mulu. Deng setan dong pung bos ju pake orang pung mulu ko kasi jalan dia pung pakariang.<bt>The mouth is like a flame (&lt;tongue of fire). We-inc can use our mouths to destroy1 many things. Our mouths can ruin/destroy2 our entire lives. Many evil things in this world come out of people's mouths. And the *devil also uses people's mouths to set in motion his work/deeds/effects/impact.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Orang su parná bekin jinak macam-macam binatang utan, binatang marayap, burung, deng ikan di laut.<bt>People have tamed various sorts of wild animals, creeping/crawling animals, birds, and fish in the sea.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="herpetoon: we have lizards, but not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">herpetoon: we have lizards, but not snakes. But using the plural for lizards seems awkward to FC</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma balóm ada satu orang ju yang parná bekin jinak dia pung mulu. Te mulu tu, satu barang jahat yang susa kaná ator. Dia sama ke racon yang marayap di badan anteru sampe bekin mati orang.<bt>But there is not.yet one single person who has ever tamed his mouth. Cuz (elaboration) the mouth, is an evil thing which is difficult to manage/control. It is like poison which crawls/creeps throughout the whole body to.point.that it kills a person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="racon"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">racon</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akatástaton: restless, unruly, wild"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">akatástaton: restless, unruly, wild</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9-10" />Deng mulu yang sama, orang puji-puji deng bamaki. Itu sonde pantas! Kotong pake mulu ko puji sang Tuhan, Allah Bapa. Ais deng itu mulu ju, kotong maki-maki orang, yang Tuhan su bekin iko Dia pung model. Karmana bisa bagitu?<bt>With the same mouth, people praise and curse each other. That is not right/appropriate! We-inc use our mouths to praise God the Father. And then with that (same) mouth also, we-inc go around cursing people, who God1 has made according to His model. How can it be like that?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maki"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">maki</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eulogoumen: speak well of, eulogize (not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">eulogoumen: speak well of, eulogize (not "praise") kataroómetha: wish evil upon, call down curses<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 1:26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Conto ke, sonde mungkin satu mata aer sama-sama maspurak kaluar aer tawar deng aer asin.<bt>For example, it is not likely/probable that one spring at the same time bursts/artesians out fresh water and salty water.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aer barisi ; pait"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">aer barisi ; pait</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peegeè: spring, fountain, source glyky ..."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">peegeè: spring, fountain, source glyky ... pikrón: fresh and sweet ... bitter, brackish, salty, not fit to drink<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Conto laen lai: sonde mungkin pohon siri babua poteka. Deng sonde mungkin jagong kasi kaluar bua anggor, to? Te pohon babua iko dia pung macam.<bt>Another example: It's not possible for the betelpepper plant to bear watermelon fruit. And it's not possible for corn to give out anggor (grape) fruit, right? [NOTE: 1st two sentences allude to two well-known Indonesian songs, the 2nd to a church song.]. Cuz (elaboration) plants/trees bear fruit according to its own type/kind.</bt><note reference="3:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, orang sonde bisa ketu bua συκῆ (<span class="Italic">suk</span>ē) dari pohon ἐλαία (<span class="Italic">elaia</span>), deng sonde bisa ketu bua ἄμπελος (<span class="Italic">ampelos</span>) dari pohon συκῆ (<span class="Italic">suk</span>ē). Dia pung maksud bilang, pohon satu macam sonde mungkin babua pohon macam laen pung. Te sonde wajar na! Itu sama ke sonde wajar kalo satu orang pake dia pung mulu ko angka puji sang Tuhan, ais nanti dia ju pake dia pung mulu tu, ko maki-maki orang.<bt>The Yunani language says people can't pick this συκῆ <span class="Italic">(sukē) </span>fruit from that ἐλαία <span class="Italic">(elaia)</span> tree, and can't pick that ἄμπελος <span class="Italic">(ampelos) </span>fruit from a συκῆ <span class="Italic">(sukē)</span> tree. Its meaning is that a tree of one kind does not bear fruit of a tree of a different kind. Cuz (elaboration) it's not natural! That's the same as it not being natural for/if/when a person uses his mouth to lift praises to God2, and then later s/he also uses that mouth of his, to curse/swear at people.</bt></note>Sama ke kotong sonde bisa timba ame aer tawar dari kolam aer asin.<bt>It's just like we-inc can't fetch fresh water from a pool of salty water.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** change RQ to statement, expanded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">*** change RQ to statement, expanded ftn 1st two sentence allude to two well-known Indonesian songs, the 2nd a church song. ; poteka<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="halykòn: salty NRSV: Can a fig"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">halykòn: salty NRSV: Can a fig tree, my brothers and sisters, yield olives, or a grapevine figs? No more can salt water yield fresh.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mana mungkin pohon siri baboa poteka?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">Mana mungkin pohon siri baboa poteka? Deng mana mungkin jagong kasi kaluar boa anggor? Te pohon baboa iko dia pung macam. Sama ke kotong sonde bisa timba ame aer tawar dari kolam aer asin.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bijaksana dari Tuhan<bt>Wisdom [+mesolectal] from God1</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Orang yang bijaksana, deng mangarti hal dong pake Tuhan pung pandangan, sonde usa angka-angka diri. Te dia tau dia pung pintar tu dari Tuhan. Biar ko dia kasi tunju dia pung pintar, deng cara dia idop lurus sa.<bt>A person who is wise, and understands things from/using God1's perspective, doesn't need to go around elevating himself/putting himself forward. Cuz (elaboration) he knows his wisdom2/cleverness is from God1. Just let him demonstrate/show his cleverness/wisdom with the way he lives a straight/just life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sophías: humility is a characteristic of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">sophías: humility is a characteristic of wise people</Message></Annotation><v n="14-15" />Jang mulu bésar bilang, lu orang bijaksana, kalo lu ada iri hati, ko, maen ru'i kasi jato orang laen. Itu sama sa deng lu tu, putar-balek. Te idop bagitu, dia pung nama su bukan &lt;bijaksana&gt; lai. Sifat ke iri hati ko, maen baru'i ko, sonde turun dari Tuhan Allah. Itu, dunya pung sifat dong. Itu, pantas kasi orang yang sonde ofer dong pung idop kasi Tuhan. Itu sifat dong iko setan dong pung jalan.<bt>Don't boast (&lt;big mouth) that you-sg are a wise person, if you are jealous/hateful, or. go around yanking at other people to make them fall (=deliberately ruining their reputations). That is just like you are corrupt/deceptive/hypocritical. Cuz (elaboration) life like that, its name is not 'wise' anymore (=can no longer be categorised as). Characteristics like jealousy/hatred or, ripping each other to shreds or, [NOTE: grammatical open disjunction, implying or other things of that sort], do not descend from God. Those are characteristics of the world. Those are appropriate for people who have not turned.over their lives to God1. Those characteristics follow the ways of the evil spirits.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="putar lida = lie ; mulu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">putar lida = lie ; mulu besar = boast ; basiku = elbow out of the way to get ahead (UNS's say elbow to get their attention</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eritheian en teei kardiaai hymoon: strife"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">eritheian en teei kardiaai hymoon: strife in your heart ánoothen katerchoménee: from heaven, which God gives epígeios: for FC, the assumption that the world system is automatically bad sounds like repudiating the goodness of Creation; where it is treated as bad, it needs to be tagged as such<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Te kalo ada iri hati deng maen baru'i, tantu ju ada kaco-balo, deng orang bekin jahat macam-macam.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if there is jealousy/hatred and ripping each other to shreds, there will certainly also be chaos/disorder and people doing all sorts of evil.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ma bijaksana yang turun datang dari Tuhan, bagini: partama-partama dia bekin kotong idop barisi. Ais dia bekin kotong ko idop deng kapala dingin, sadia mangala, salalu sabar, deng kalam. Dia pung hasil ju bekin kotong bae hati, suka tolong orang, sonde barát sablá, deng sonde muka-balakang deng orang laen dong.<bt>But wisdom which descends coming from God1, is like this: first of all it makes us-inc live clean/pure. And then it makes us live cool-headed (=peace-loving), prepared to yield/give in, always patient, and stable/not easily upset. It also produces good will in us-inc, liking to help people, impartial/unbiased, and not hypocritical (&lt;front-back) with other people. [DISCOURSE: Order rearranged 1) general, 2) emphasis on internal attitudes, 3) emph on external relations].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Order rearranged 1) general, 2) emphasis"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">Order rearranged 1) general, 2) emphasis on internal attitudes, 3) emph on external relations: kapala dingin = calm, cool-headed, peace-loving ; muka-balakang = muka dua ; hati puti barisi = bae hati ; mangala = mengalah ; boa = male genitals</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hee dè ánoothen sophía: abstract --"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">hee dè ánoothen sophía: abstract -- da guys? and so on eireenikee: in the context of the next verse, it's promoting harmony, more than experiencing inner peace.<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>epieikees: equanimity, gentleness, forbearance. eupeithees: obedient, compliant. Probably "make nice" fits best, rather than "make friends".<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>adiákritos: without prejudices</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Deng orang yang kasi tunju jalan dame nanti dapa hasil yang bae. Itu sama ke orang tanam bibit, ko lama-lama dia dapa kambali dia pung hasil yang bae.<bt>And people who show the way to be at peace will later get good results. That is like a person planting seed, so that eventually he can get a good result/harvest in return. [EXEG: NLT]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang iko dunya pung mau-mau<bt>Don't follow the desires of the world [NOTE: Kupang church circles are used to personifying "the world"]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Bosong ada maen bakanjar deng babakalai satu deng satu. Dia pung pasal apa? Itu tagal di bosong pung teng-tenga ada orang dong yang usaha karás ko mau cari sanáng kasi dia pung diri sandiri sa.<bt>You-pl are often arguing and fighting with each other. What's the reason for that (Idiom: what is the paragraph for that?) It is because among you-pl there are people who are striving very hard to find ways to just please themselves.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasal apa? = source (UNS ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">pasal apa? = source (UNS = sebab)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="strateuoménoon: each desire trying to win"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">strateuoménoon: each desire trying to win against the other desires inside you mélesin: different parts of the body<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>heedonais: selfish desires, lusts, pleasures that conflict with Christian conduct, in the New Testament. Can be physical desires, or desires that come in conflict with what other people want</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Bosong banafsu mau dapa satu barang, ma tangan sonde sampe ko ga'e ame sang dia. Ais bosong iri hati, maen bakanjar, deng babakalai, sampe bosong sonde tanggong-tanggong deng mau bunu orang.<bt>You-pl lust after something, but your hand doesn't reach far enough to hook it in. So you are jealous/hateful, argumentative, and fighting with each other, to.point.that it's not beyond you to want to kill someone (Idiom: carry-carry with wanting to kill).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tanggong-tanggong deng babunu = sonde takut,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">tanggong-tanggong deng babunu = sonde takut, anggap biasa</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tagal bosong sonde sambayang, deng sonde minta dari Tuhan, andia ko bosong sonde dapa apa yang bosong minta.<bt>Because you-pl don't pray, and don't ask from God1, that is why you don't get/receive it (=what you ask for). [EXEG: Martin p.147 suggests this is request wisdom referring back to 1:5. Make it explicit if UNS's go off into outer space. (Although a simple word for ‘wisdom’ is problematic in most of our lgs.)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tangan sonde sampe ko ga'e sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">tangan sonde sampe ko ga'e sang dia = unable to obtain it ; sonde tanggong-tanggong = nothing hinders them ; Proverb = Maksud hati ingin memeluk gunung. Apa daya tangan tak sampai.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phoneúete: you commit murder &quot;kill peopo&quot;:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">phoneúete: you commit murder "kill peopo": to some "murda" is English zeeloute: "um" would sound like the person you intend to murder; "da kine" refers to the thing you want. On second reading "um" seemed better<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>máchesthe: order parallel to 4:1 shows the association; reproducing the chiasm loses it. Pidgin isn't into chiasms. aiteisthai: "aks" loses the information that he's talking about praying, so "God" needs to be added. "pray" implies God<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ma biar bosong sambayang putus kayu batu ju, bosong sonde dapa apa yang bosong minta, tagal bosong cuma minta iko bosong pung nafsu sandiri sa.<bt>But even though/if you-pl pray fervently/long-winded (Idiom: breaking a tree trunk), you-pl don't get what you ask for, because you only ask according to your own lusts/desires. [NOTE to daughter translations: Basically, no other languages have a “nafsu (Arabic loan)” word. So make sure the selfish element is prominent (CEV). Careful that it's not limited to sexual passions, as is implied by some English translations. ALT: “because you only ask according to your own thoughts to fulfill your selfish plans”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sambayang putus kayu batu = fervent,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">sambayang putus kayu batu = fervent, earnest</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kakoos: from wrong motives, with bad"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">kakoos: from wrong motives, with bad purposes heedonais: same as verse 1<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dasar orang sonde satia! Bosong sama ke pasangan yang sonde satia deng maen serong. Kalo bosong ika diri deng dunya pung mau-mau, bosong bekin diri bamusu deng Tuhan Allah. Itu su!<bt>You people are fundamentally unfaithful/disloyal! [DISCOURSE: Resonating the language of a curse or extreme disgust.] You-pl are like a pairing/couple who is not faithful and commits adultery. If you bind yourselves to the desires of the world, you make yourselves enemies with God. That's how it is!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="5Ts setia &gt; satia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">5Ts setia &gt; satia</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="moichalídes: probably in the same sense"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">moichalídes: probably in the same sense as the prophets used it, for spiritual adultery: you belong to God, and you're prostituting yourselves</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Andia ko Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan su taro Dia pung Roh di botong pung hati. Deng itu Roh pung mau, ko botong satia tarús deng Dia sa. Te Dia tu, camburu.&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why the Scripture writes saying, “God1 has placed His Spirit in our-exc livers. And that Spirit desires that we-exc are always faithful just to Him. Cuz (elaboration) He, is jealous/envious.” [NOTE to daughter translations: since /satia/ is often a difficult concept to translate, make sure the relationship between /satia/ and /camburu/ comes out clear in the result. Consider: /...botong ta'ika tarús sang Dia sa. Dia mara kalo kotong ta'ika deng orang/bos (?) laen./ Or reorder as ALT: “He is jealous/envious. That is why that Holy Spirit desires that we-exc are always faithful to just Him.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added note to daughter translations"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">***added note to daughter translations</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hee grapheè: not the whole Bible,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">hee grapheè: not the whole Bible, but the part that was available at that time, the Old Testament. Not a quotation tò pneuma: the spirit built in at creation (TEV), which makes verse 6 more of a climax "God does even better than that". Could be the Holy Spirit, but that doesn't match the flow of thought. RSV has God as subject, extremely concerned about the spirit he put into us<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Tamba lai, Tuhan Allah masi mau kasi tamba Dia pung hati bae ju. Andia ko Tulisan Barisi tulis bilang:<bt>Furthermore, God still wants to increase His kindness/goodness/grace also. That is why the Scripture writes, saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan lawan orang yang tinggi hati dong,<bt>“God1 opposes people who are high-livered (=proud/arrogant/boastful),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Dia kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang orang yang randá hati dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>but He shows His kindness/goodness/grace to people who are low-livered (=humble/modest).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tinggi hati = sombong ; randa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">tinggi hati = sombong ; randa hati</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="légei: Proverbs 3:34"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">légei: Proverbs 3:34</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kata-kata Mutiara 3:34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Tuhan Allah tu, kotong pung Bos yang hak parenta sang kotong! Jadi sarakan bosong pung diri sang Dia, ko iko Dia pung mau. Bosong jang iko setan dong pung bos pung mau. Lawan karás sang dia. Deng bagitu, dia lari kasi tenga sang bosong.<bt>God1 is our-inc Boss who has the say-so/ordering rights over us-inc! So (consequently) surrender/turn over yourselves to Him, to follow/obey His will. You-pl should not follow/obey the desires of the *devil. Oppose him forcefully. In that way he will run away leaving you behind.</bt><v n="8-9" />Usaha ko bosong idop satu hati deng Tuhan Allah. Deng bagitu, Dia ju deka-deka deng bosong.<bt>Strive to live one livered (in harmony/in accord/same purpose) with God. In that way, He will also be very near you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Weh, bosong yang idop kamomos dong! Bosong musti bekin lurus bosong pung jalan idop. Deng bosong yang hati bacabang dong! Bosong musti jalan lurus iko sang Tuhan, deng jang baserong kiri-kanan lai. Salama ini bosong idop sanáng-sanáng deng bakiki-kaka sa. Jadi sakarang bosong stop su! Bosong su tau bosong pung hati bacabang deng bosong pung sala-sala dong. Lebe bae bosong manyasal deng manangis makarereu su.<bt>Weh, you who live in filth/defilement/moral corruption! You must straighten out the way you-pl are living. And those of you who are undecided/doubtful (branched liver)! You-pl must follow the straight path obeying God1, and don't deviate left-right off track any more. Up until now you-pl have been living happily/without stress/in luxury and just laughing with pleasure (Idiom). So now need to stop that! You-pl know your wavering/indecisiveness/doubting, and your wrongs. It would be better for you to be remorseful/sorry and cry with grief. [DISCOURSE: STYLE: note NLT explication; otherwise there is no answer to “Why should these people be like this? What's the problem?”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati bacabang = undecided, hati mendua,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">hati bacabang = undecided, hati mendua, bimbang ; baserong bakiki-kaka = ketawa yang sanang mati pung ***combine 8-9<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="enggísate: come close, develop a close"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">enggísate: come close, develop a close relationship</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Kalo bosong batúl-batúl mangarti bilang, bosong memang sonde pantas di Tuhan Allah pung muka, nanti Dia angka bosong jadi orang yang pantas di Dia pung muka.<bt>If you-pl really understand that you are truly not worthy to be before God, then He will later lift/elevate you to be people who are worthy to be before Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi besar hati = make brave"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">kasi besar hati = make brave</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang omong bekin busuk orang<bt>Don't say bad things about people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Sodara dong! Jang omong bekin busuk bosong satu deng satu pung nama bae. Te kalo bosong su omong bagitu, deng maen lempar sala tarús kasi orang, bosong su langgar Tuhan pung atoran yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu musti sayang lu pung sodara, sama ke lu sayang lu pung diri sandiri.&gt;&gt; Deng kalo bosong sonde iko itu atoran bagitu, bosong su angka diri lebe tinggi dari Tuhan pung Atoran.<bt>Siblings! Don't say bad things ruining each other's reputations/name. Cuz (elaboration) if you speak that way, and keep throwing wrong at people, you have already violated/transgressed God1's regulation which says, “You-sg must love/pity your sibling, just as you love your own self.” And if you-pl don't follow that regulation in that way, you have elevated yourselves above/higher than God1's Law.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katalaleite: more like putting down somebody"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">katalaleite: more like putting down somebody than ruining his reputation, though the word overlaps with blaspheemein nomos in these two verses concentrates on the negative, Old Testament aspect of the Law of Moses, rather than on the full scale, positive view of the whole thing that has the Gospel at its center (1:25, 2:8-12). So here it may be okay to just say "Da Rules From God". On the other hand, what he says can go with the positive view of Law as part of the Gospel, so we might want to recast it.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Cuma Tuhan sandiri yang susun itu Atoran, yang ada pung hak ko putus kotong pung parkara. Cuma Dia sandiri yang ada pung hak kasi salamat kotong, ko, kasi hukum mati sang kotong. Bosong sonde ada pung hak ko putus orang pung parkara, ko, omong bekin busuk orang pung nama bae.<bt>Only God1 himself, who compiled that Law, has the right to decide/judge our-inc court.case. Only He himself in the one who has the right to *save us-inc, or, give us the death penalty. You-pl don't have the right to decide people's court.case, or, ruin people's good reputation/name.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="soozein: save, take out of trouble."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">soozein: save, take out of trouble. But here it's more like eternal destiny</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang mulu bésar<bt>Don't boast/talk big (lit: big mouth)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ALT Title: Whatever we plan, don't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">ALT Title: Whatever we plan, don't forget God</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Bagini! Bosong tu, su musti tau ko jang omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini hari ko beso, botong mau pi di itu kota sana, é! Botong ada mau tenga di sana barang satu taon. Deng botong mau jadi papalele ko dapa ontong sadiki doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Like this! You-pl, should already know better than to say, “Today or tomorrow, we-exc want to go to that city over there, é! We-exc are going to stay there for about a year. And we-exc are going to do small-scale commerce to get some profit!” [DISCOURSE: STYLE: understatement: “get a little profit”, meaning “we expect to rake in huge profits”].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="understatement @@"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">understatement @@</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Lu tau apa so'al beso-beso? Sonde ada orang yang tau idop pung mau-mau. Manusia pung idop sama ke kabut yang kantara sabantar sa, ais ju ilang buang.<bt>What do you know about the future? There is not one person who knows what's going to happen in the future (Idiom: life's various desires). A human's life is like fog which is visible for just a moment, and then disappears.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="beso-beso = indefinite time in future"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">beso-beso = indefinite time in future ; beso-lusa is open-ended ; idop pung mau-mau</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ouk epistasthe to tees aurion poia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">ouk epistasthe to tees aurion poia hee zooee hymoon: You do not know anything about tomorrow, what sort of thing your life will be</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:13-14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kata-kata Mutiara 27:1</note><v n="15" />Lebe bae bosong omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo Tuhan sayang, na, biar ko kotong idop. Deng kalo Tuhan mau, biar ko kotong bisa bekin bagini.&gt;&gt;<bt>It would be better to say, “If God1 loves/pities, na, we may be able to live (also figurative: make a living). And if God1 wants, we may be able to do this.” [DISCOURSE: STYLE: First sentence is conventionalised Kupang phrase for "if God wills"] [NOTE to daughter translations: check how local language would say it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo Tuhan sayang = is fixed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">Kalo Tuhan sayang = is fixed phrase, kehendaki?, mengizinkan</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Te kalo sonde omong bagitu, bosong cuma mulu bésar sa. Itu sama ke bosong su lupa buang sang Tuhan di bosong pung rancana dong. Itu su sala bésar!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if (you) don't speak like that, you-pl are just boasting/mouthing off. It is as if you-pl have completely forgotten/left out God1 from your plans. That's a big mistake/wrong/sin!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Inga bae-bae! Orang yang su tau apa yang batúl, ma sonde bekin iko bagitu, itu sama sa deng dia su bekin sala.<bt>Remember this well! People/A person who knows what is right, but doesn't do according to that, it is the same as s/he has done wrong/sin.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalon poiein: do something good, noble,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">kalon poiein: do something good, noble, beautiful</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang kaya yang sonde idop lurus dong, musti ati-ati<bt>Rich people who aren't straight (=honest, fair) must watch out</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1-6" />Bosong orang kaya dong! Pasang talinga ko dengar bae-bae! Bosong tahan ame gaji dari orang yang karjá banting tulang kasi bosong. Sakarang dong pung hasil karingat ada batarea kasi tau bosong pung putar-balek. Tantu Tuhan Allah yang Paling Hebat su taro talinga sang itu orang karjá dong pung susa.<bt>You-pl rich people. Fasten on your ears to listen carefully (=pay close attention)! You-pl hold back/withhold wages from people who work hard (&lt;Idiom) for you. Now their efforts/sweat is shouting out making known your deception/fraud. Certainly God who is Most Amazing, has placed his ears (=paid attention to, heard the complaints of) on those workers' difficulties. [DISCOURSE: 1-6 combined so as to present evil first, then coming consequences (at Marge Crofts' suggestion) ORDER: 1a, 4-6, 1b-3; NOTE there was nothing wrong with the previous version, it was just felt this reorganisation carries the point better.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***vs.1-6 combined so present evil first,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">***vs.1-6 combined so present evil first, then coming consequences (at Marge Crofts' suggestion) 1a, 4-6, 1b-3; NOTE there was nothing wrong with the previous version, it was just felt this reorganisation might carry the point better. tahan ame gaji =<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ameesántoon: have been harvesting your crops"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">ameesántoon: have been harvesting your crops for you by cutting krázei: cries out. In Greek it's the money crying out metaphorically; but in Pidgin we could couple it with the "shouts of the harvesters" in the next clause<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>kyríou sabaoòth: from the Old Testament = God as commander of the heavenly armies</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:1-6a" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 24:14-15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Bosong pung karjá di ini dunya ni, andia cuma bekin enak bosong pung diri sandiri, deng idop leha-leha sa. Sakarang bosong su sama ke sapi gumuk yang siap kaná horo. Bosong su hukum deng bunu bekin mati orang bae dong, yang sonde bisa bela diri di bosong pung muka.<bt>Your-pl work on this earth here, is only pleasing yourselves (implication of satisfying one's senses), and just living a life of total leisure. Now you are like fat cows ready to be slaughtered. You-pl have punished and killed good people, who couldn't protect/defend themselves before you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="idop leha-leha = idop ongkang-ongkang kaki"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">idop leha-leha = idop ongkang-ongkang kaki = sitting around in total leisure, letting others do the work, hidup bersenang-senang ; bontak-bontak =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="etrypheésate: led lives of luxury, self-indulgence,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">etrypheésate: led lives of luxury, self-indulgence, carousing, revelry espataleésate: lived voluptuously, in indulgence; also used of a frisky sheep living it up in rich pasture<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>ethrépsate taas kardias hymoon: like cattle in a feeding pen, their hearts set on getting as fat as they can, not realizing that the butcher is waiting for them tòn díkaion: the righteous person (generic) = righteous people</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Orang kaya dong! Mulai manangis makarereu su! Te nanti sangsara macam-macam nae kaná sang bosong. Bosong pung harta-benda su mulai ancor buang. Deng bosong pung pakean bagus dong, fufuk makan buang. Bosong pung mas-perak dong su sonde ada harga lai. Deng nanti itu mas-perak dong makan bale sang bosong, sama ke api makan buang kayu karíng. Karmana ko dunya su mau kiamat, ma bosong masi batasibu kumpul itu harta mati dong? Bosong pung harta sandiri nanti jadi bukti bilang, bosong sonde mangarti yang mana yang ada pung harga di Tuhan pung mata!<bt>(You) rich people! (You) ought to be crying with grief! Cuz (elaboration) later various sorts of suffering/misery will overwhelm/attack you-pl. Your-pl belongings/riches/wealth has begun to destruct. And your good/fine clothes, 1) insects (moths/wood-boring insects) have been/are being eaten up [as NVV], OR 2) are being slowly eaten to dust [as SVC=VVV]. Your-pl gold-silver (=wealthy, expensive things) have no more value. And later those gold-silver things will come back and consume you, just like fire consumes dry wood. How is it that the world is about to end, but you-pl are still acting like busybodies gathering together that useless wealth/belongings? Your own wealth/belongings will be evidence/proof that you do not understand which (categories of things) are the ones that have value in God1's eyes!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="klaúsate: weep or cry, used for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">klaúsate: weep or cry, used for mourning the dead, lamenting over what they know is going to happen to a city, any feeling of sadness, care, or anxiety; weep for someone ololúzontes: cry out in joy or pain<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>talaipooríais: terrible things, sufferings; wretchedness, misery, things to lament about séseepen: rotted, as applied to grains and fruit. With wealth, it could mean it has all become worthless, like stock in a company that folds gégonen: phrased as though it had already happened, even though it hasn't. The prophet is saying "I see your wealth rotted away, your clothes moth-eaten"<span class="Italic">(1) (1) (1) (1) (1) </span>chrysòs: gold doesn't rust, and the tarnish on silver doesn't destroy it, so this has to be a metaphor; but the metaphor carries over into the next clause katíootai: rusted, tarnished, covered with corrosionmartýrion: testifies that all you have to show for your life is a pile of worthless junk, OR that the tarnished goodies will stand as evidence of how worthless all this material wealth is phágetai: destroy, literally "eat up" the way fire eats up what it burnsetheesaurísate: you are going to find that all this stuff you have stashed for yourself ends up as evidence against you, shows up to make you miserable</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="fufuk makan buang SVC, not NVV"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">fufuk makan buang SVC, not NVV makan bale = barang merugikan ; harta mati = belongings that can't be used for anything</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:1-6b" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 6:19</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sabar dalam susa<bt>Be patient in difficulty</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Sodara dong! Bosong musti sabar tunggu Tuhan pung datang kambali. Lia sa orang tani yang ada sabar tunggu dia pung hasil tana. Ujan partama datang, ju dia batanam. Ais itu, dia tunggu ujan lai ko bekin subur dia pung tanaman. Lama-lama ju dong babua. Pas dia pung waktu datang, itu orang pi koru dia pung hasil tanam dong.<bt>Siblings! You-pl must be patient waiting for God1/Lord's return again. Just look at a farmer who is patiently awaiting the produce of the land. The first rain comes, and.so he plants. After that, he waits for more rain to make his plants fertile/luxuriant. Eventually they bear fruit. Then right at the right time, that person goes and picks/harvests the produce (pl) of his planting.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makararapak = impatient ; sabar hati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">makararapak = impatient ; sabar hati ; hasil tana ; hasil tanam ; precious/valuable &gt; implicit</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makrothymeésate: aorist for a process, therefore"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">makrothymeésate: aorist for a process, therefore "start hanging in there" geoorgòs: the farmer, again generic -- farmers in general<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>próïmon, ópsimon: In Palestinian agriculture, there are early rains, in the fall, starting light in late October and November and heavier December to February; late rains, in the spring, March and April. They put the grain crops in the ground in November or later. They are harvested in April at the coast to June or July in the mountains</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Bosong ju musti sabar bagitu. Bekin kuat diri, te sonde lama lai, Tuhan su datang, andia tu!<bt>You-pl must be patient like that. Strengthen yourselves, cuz (elaboration) it won't be long, (before) God1/Lord has come. That's how it is!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="steeriksate taas kardias hymoon: make your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">steeriksate taas kardias hymoon: make your hearts be firmly based</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Sodara dong! Jang bamangomel. Mangomel sa tarús, te nanti Tuhan yang putus hukuman sang lu! Lia sa, te Bapatua Hakim di atas, su badiri di bosong pung muka idong.<bt>Siblings! Don't be grumbling/complaining about/to each other. Just go ahead and complain. cuz (elaboration) later God1 is the one who will decide your-sg punishment! [+irony, sarcasm]. You-ll see, cuz (elaboration) the Old Man/Senior Judge up there is standing right in front of your nose.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangomek = mengeluh, mengomel, grumble, gripe,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">mangomek = mengeluh, mengomel, grumble, gripe, complain ; Mangomek sa tarús, te nanti Tuhan yang hukum sang lu! = irony, sarcasm ; muka idong = very close (in time or space), will happen very soon ; ujian su di muka idong, ma lu masi bahaha-hihi/ bakaka-kiki (bersenang-senang)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meè stenázete: don't grumble about anybody,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">meè stenázete: don't grumble about anybody, place blame, bicker, gripe about your troubles prò tóon thyróon: right outside the door (or gate) on his way inside<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Sodara dong! Iko conto dari Tuhan pung jubir dong. Biar dong dapa susa macam-macam, ma dong tahan susa tarús.<bt>Siblings! Follow the example of God1's spokesmen/*prophets. Even though they experienced various sorts of difficulties, they nevertheless continued to endure difficulties.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hypódeigma: example to follow"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">hypódeigma: example to follow</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Kalo ada orang yang tahan susa, kotong suka angka-angka itu orang pung nama. Conto ke ba'i Ayub. Dia dapa susa macam-macam, ma dia tahan banting sa. Ais Tuhan jato kasian sang dia, ju Dia ator samua jadi bae kasi sang Ayub. Tuhan bekin bagitu, tagal Dia hati bae deng ponu sayang.<bt>If there is a person who endures difficulties, we-inc like to lift up/praise that person's name/reputation. An example is Gf Ayub (=Job). He got various sorts of difficulties, but he just endured (the abuse). So God1 had pity/compassion on him, and He arranged for everything to become good for Ayub. God1 did that, because His liver is good and full of love. (OR because He is kindhearted/caring/generous and full of love.)</bt><note reference="5:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ayub 1:21-22, 2:10, Lagu Puji dong 103:8; Yakobis 1:2-3, 12</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">So'al sumpa<bt>Concerning oaths</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Sodara dong! Yang pantíng, bosong jang ba'angka sumpa. Kalo mau bilang &lt;&lt;hoo&gt;&gt;, na, manyao &lt;&lt;hoo&gt;&gt; sa. Deng kalo mau bilang &lt;&lt;sonde&gt;&gt;, na, manyao &lt;&lt;sonde&gt;&gt; sa. Bagitu su cukup! Jang talebe-lebe deng ba'angka sumpa yang subu orang mati di bumi. Apalai basumpa &lt;&lt;demi Tuhan&gt;&gt; yang idop di langit. Sonde ada pung guna angka sumpa macam-macam. Te kalo bagitu, na, tarima barisi lu pung hukuman, tagal lu pung sumpa dong.<bt>Siblings! It's important that you-pl not swear oaths (that you will do something). If you want to say “yes”, then just answer/respond “yes”. And if you want to say “no”, then just answer/respond “no”. That's sufficient! Don't overdo/go overboard by swearing an oath that mentions dead people on earth. Not even oaths that are “by God1” who lives in the sky/heaven. There is no need/use to swear various sorts of oaths. Cuz (elaboration) if you do that, you must accept the punishment you deserve (=accept cleanly), because of your oaths.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sumpa putus kayu batu = long"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">sumpa putus kayu batu = long and elaborate; sumpa ~ cumpa (Air Mata, and rural), tarima barisi =</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:34-37</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">So'al sambayang yang bawa hasil<bt>About prayer that brings results</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Kalo ada di bosong yang dapa susa, lebe bae dia sambayang. Deng kalo ada yang sanáng, lebe bae dia manyanyi puji-puji sang Tuhan.<bt>If there is among you-pl someone who experiences difficulty, it would be good for him to pray. And if there is someone who is happy, if would be good for him to sing praises to God1.</bt><v n="14" />Kalo ada di bosong yang saki, na, lebe bae pange datang sang tua-tua jama'at dong. Minta ko dong taro minya di itu orang saki, deng sambayang bawa Tuhan pung nama, ko biar Tuhan bekin dia bae.<bt>If there is among you-pl someone who is sick, na, it would be good to call/summon the elders/leader of the congregation. Ask them to put oil on that sick person, and pray bearing God1's/Lord's name/reputation, so that God1 would make him well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="minya bebahaa = orang Rote pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">minya bebahaa = orang Rote pung minya obat (minya kalapa, clover roots, shallots)</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 6:13</note><v n="15" />Deng kalo bosong sambayang kasi orang saki, deng parcaya batúl-batúl sang Tuhan, nanti Tuhan bekin bae sang itu orang. Deng kalo itu orang su bekin sala, Tuhan nanti hapus buang dia pung sala-sala dong.<bt>And if/when you-pl pray for sick people, and truly believe in God1, then God1 will heal that person. And if that person has done wrong/sins, God1 will *forgive (erase away) his wrongs.</bt><v n="16" />Kalo ada di bosong yang bekin sala, na, bosong musti bamangaku bosong pung sala dong. Deng bagitu, bosong basambayang satu kasi satu, ko biar bosong jadi bae.<bt>If there is among you-pl someone who does wrong, na, you-pl must reciprocally confess your wrongs. In that way, you should pray for each other, so that you can be/become well/healed/right relationships.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Orang yang pung hati barisi, dia pung sambayang ponu deng kuasa, deng bisa bawa hasil yang bae.<bt>A person who has a clean/pure liver, his prayer is full of power/authority, and can bring a good result.</bt><v n="17" />Ame conto dari ba'i Elia. Dia tu, manusia biasa sama ke kotong ju. Ma waktu dia sambayang minta ko jang ujan lai, ju ujan barenti memang, deng sonde turun-turun sampe tiga taon satenga.<bt>Take the example of Gf/Ff Elia. He was a normal human as we-inc are also. But when he prayed asking for it to not rain anymore, the rain stopped right away, and didn't descend again for 3 years 1/2.</bt><note reference="5:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 17:1, 18:1</note><v n="18" />Ais ju dia sambayang minta ko ujan turun, ju ujan turun datang memang. Rumput jadi ijo, deng kabón dong bawa hasil kambali.<bt>And then he prayed asking for the rain to descend, and the rain descended coming right away. The grass turned green, and the food.gardens/fields brought produce again.</bt><note reference="5:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 18:42-45</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Sodara dong! Kalo ada di bosong yang mulai bekin sala, ko, jalan kasi tenga apa yang batúl, ais ada yang tolong sang dia ko kambali pi Tuhan pung jalan lurus, itu bae.<bt>Siblings! If there is among you-pl someone who begins to do wrong, or, leaves behind what is true/correct, and then there is someone who helps him return to God1's straight path/way, that is good.</bt><v n="20" />Inga ini bae-bae! Kalo bosong tolong orang yang bekin sala, ko dia datang kambali pi Tuhan, deng dia sonde bekin sala lai, bosong su kasi salamat itu orang ko biar dia dapa idop tarús deng Tuhan. Deng bagitu, Tuhan su hapus buang dia pung sala bam-banya.<bt>Remember this well! If/when you-pl help a person who does wrong, so that he come back to God1, and he doesn't do wrong anymore, you-pl have *saved that person so that he can live continually with God1. In that way, God1 has erased away his many wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mal'unuk = heaps of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z">mal'unuk = heaps of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalýpsei: hide by getting them taken"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:07:21Z" status="Information">kalýpsei: hide by getting them taken care of, not just suppressing them as in 16</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kata-kata Mutiara 10:12, 1 Petrus 4:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Bagitu su!<bt>That's all!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dari beta,<bt>From me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yakobis<bt>Kobis</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>